France allows artificial insemination for lesbians and singles
In France, artificial fertilisation will also be open to women and lesbians living alone in the future: the Paris National Assembly voted by a large majority for a government bill allowing all women to claim in vitro fertilisation, which is likely to increase the demand for anonymous sperm donations significantly.
