The programme, launched in 1980, selects refugees from UN camps around the world and resettles them in the US. The ceiling of 18,000 refugees for the 2020 budget year would be the lowest in the programme’s history. Even the current upper limit of 30,000 is a low. When US President Donald Trump’s predecessor Barack Obama left the White House, the figure was almost 85,000.
